javascript
@section Scripts {
<script>
    function onLabourGridDataBound(e) {
        var grid = e.sender;
        var gridName = grid.element.attr('id'); // Gets grid ID like "LabourDetailsGrid_123"
        
        // Grid-specific dataSource binding
        grid.dataSource.unbind("change");
        grid.dataSource.bind("change", function() {
            updateToolbarButtons(gridName);
        });
        
        // Initial update
        updateToolbarButtons(gridName);
    }

    function updateToolbarButtons(gridName) {
        var grid = $("#" + gridName).data("kendoGrid");
        var hasChanges = grid.hasChanges();
        
        // Grid-specific button selection
        var saveButton = $("#" + gridName).find(".k-grid-save-changes");
        var addButton = $("#" + gridName).find(".k-grid-add");
        
        saveButton.prop("disabled", !hasChanges)
                 .toggleClass("k-state-disabled", !hasChanges);
        addButton.prop("disabled", hasChanges)
                 .toggleClass("k-state-disabled", hasChanges);
    }
</script>
}

<style>
    /* Grid-specific disabled styling */
    #LabourDetailsGrid_@ViewBag.PartNum .k-grid-save-changes:disabled,
    #LabourDetailsGrid_@ViewBag.PartNum .k-grid-save-changes.k-state-disabled,
    #LabourDetailsGrid_@ViewBag.PartNum .k-grid-add:disabled,
    #LabourDetailsGrid_@ViewBag.PartNum .k-grid-add.k-state-disabled {
        opacity: 0.6;
        cursor: not-allowed;
        background-color: #f5f5f5 !important;
        border-color: #ddd !important;
        color: #999 !important;
        background-image: none;
        pointer-events: none;
    }
</style>
Key Improvements:

Explicit Grid Identification

Uses grid.element.attr('id') to get the unique grid ID

Directly references grid by ID in all selectors

Dual State Management

Sets both disabled property and k-state-disabled class

Handles both <button> and <a> element types

Grid-Specific CSS

Uses your grid's actual ID in CSS selectors

Combines pseudo-class and Kendo state class

pointer-events: none prevents any interaction

Verification Steps:

Check grid ID in browser console:

javascript
console.log('Grid ID:', $('#LabourDetailsGrid_@ViewBag.PartNum').attr('id'));
Verify button states after changes:

javascript
// In updateToolbarButtons():
console.log('Grid:', gridName, 'HasChanges:', hasChanges);
console.log('Save disabled:', saveButton.prop('disabled'));
console.log('Add disabled:', addButton.prop('disabled'));
